WEBVTT


00:01:01.542 --> 00:01:03.544
EPISODE 11

00:01:03.627 --> 00:01:04.503
You're getting off work late.

00:01:05.087 --> 00:01:06.171
There's a shoot tomorrow,

00:01:06.255 --> 00:01:07.840
so I had to prepare before I left.

00:01:14.054 --> 00:01:15.764
-Excuse me, Chair Kim.
-What?

00:01:15.848 --> 00:01:17.224
When might you be available?

00:01:17.308 --> 00:01:18.475
Why do you ask?

00:01:18.559 --> 00:01:20.227
I think it's time for a new profile photo.

00:01:20.311 --> 00:01:22.605
You've been in the media a lot these days.

00:01:22.688 --> 00:01:24.940
We can talk about that some other time!

00:01:34.241 --> 00:01:35.492
The exit passcode is different.

00:02:10.069 --> 00:02:12.196
Seol-ah.

00:02:13.405 --> 00:02:14.365
We need to get out of here.

00:04:01.555 --> 00:04:02.556
That's right.

00:04:03.265 --> 00:04:05.017
This is where you belong.

00:04:16.695 --> 00:04:18.155
-Let's go.
-Okay.

00:04:28.499 --> 00:04:31.502
When will the job be finished?

00:04:32.086 --> 00:04:33.378
Hurry up.

00:04:34.213 --> 00:04:37.091
Get it done before the insurance company
or the police find it.

00:04:38.383 --> 00:04:39.301
Are you okay?

00:04:41.595 --> 00:04:42.971
Did you find

00:04:44.098 --> 00:04:45.140
what you were looking for?

00:04:46.475 --> 00:04:47.559
They were all there.

00:04:48.393 --> 00:04:51.396
The Taemyung pieces,
the ones Chair Kim had switched out,

00:04:53.023 --> 00:04:54.733
and even my father's painting.

00:04:57.361 --> 00:04:59.863
Every family photo I had
was lost in the fire,

00:05:00.864 --> 00:05:02.741
but the last memory of my family

00:05:03.784 --> 00:05:05.452
was locked inside that vault.

00:05:07.913 --> 00:05:10.874
I'll never forgive Chair Kim.

00:05:12.167 --> 00:05:13.919
I'll make her pay for what she did.

00:05:15.462 --> 00:05:16.463
I'll be by your side

00:05:17.714 --> 00:05:18.966
the whole way.

00:05:42.197 --> 00:05:43.323
Enjoy the auction.

00:06:08.891 --> 00:06:09.933
Is everything ready?

00:06:41.548 --> 00:06:43.008
SEARCH AND SEIZURE WARRANT
ARREST WARRANT

00:06:58.774 --> 00:07:00.025
Untitled by Lee Soo-dam

00:07:00.108 --> 00:07:02.861
has been sold to a floor bidder
for 400 million won.

00:07:02.945 --> 00:07:04.112
Congratulations.

00:07:14.831 --> 00:07:19.211
This unpublished masterpiece
is said to be the final work

00:07:19.294 --> 00:07:20.796
by Artist Song Hwan-ju.

00:07:21.713 --> 00:07:23.757
Its estimated value
exceeds seven billion won,

00:07:23.840 --> 00:07:25.008
and it's expected to surpass

00:07:25.092 --> 00:07:27.594
the artist's most famous work,
Cheong-myeong.

00:07:33.267 --> 00:07:34.351
However,

00:07:34.434 --> 00:07:38.230
I will not be putting it up
for auction today.

00:07:43.193 --> 00:07:44.653
The reason is that it's not authentic.

00:07:45.737 --> 00:07:47.447
-What?
-It's not authentic?

00:07:49.533 --> 00:07:52.786
This artwork was submitted
through unofficial channels

00:07:52.869 --> 00:07:54.329
-What is she saying?
-under the orders of Chair Kim Sun-ae

00:07:54.413 --> 00:07:55.789
at Royal Auction.

00:07:56.915 --> 00:07:58.834
I questioned its authenticity

00:07:58.917 --> 00:08:00.877
and sent it
for professional authentication.

00:08:00.961 --> 00:08:02.713
-The results showed
-What is she doing?

00:08:02.796 --> 00:08:05.132
-the use of an industrial synthetic resin
-Ms. Han!

00:08:05.215 --> 00:08:06.758
-rather than the natural glue
-What the hell are you doing?

00:08:06.842 --> 00:08:10.095
Artist Song typically used
in their collage works.

00:08:10.178 --> 00:08:12.306
ART AUTHENTICATION REPORT: FORGERY

00:08:23.191 --> 00:08:24.693
Even the signature is different.

00:08:25.193 --> 00:08:26.820
SIGNATURE COMPARISON ANALYSIS
FORGERY / GENUINE

00:08:26.903 --> 00:08:28.655
The character for "hwan," which means
"to shine," in the artist's name

00:08:28.739 --> 00:08:30.615
is incorrectly written,
using the "child" radical

00:08:30.699 --> 00:08:32.492
instead of the correct "fire" radical.

00:08:32.576 --> 00:08:33.827
You idiot!

00:08:33.910 --> 00:08:36.663
The authentication agency has confirmed

00:08:36.747 --> 00:08:40.292
that this piece is a complete forgery.

00:08:40.375 --> 00:08:42.210
Get her. Drag her down.

00:08:42.294 --> 00:08:43.128
Yes, ma'am.

00:08:43.211 --> 00:08:44.046
That crazy…

00:08:54.765 --> 00:08:58.435
We've also obtained evidence
that the Taemyung pieces lost in the fire

00:08:58.518 --> 00:09:01.021
were also forgeries.

00:09:01.104 --> 00:09:03.357
Hey, get her out of here!
What are you doing?

00:09:03.440 --> 00:09:06.026
Damn it! No photos!

00:09:06.109 --> 00:09:08.779
Then where are the authentic pieces?

00:09:16.536 --> 00:09:17.371
As you can see,

00:09:17.454 --> 00:09:20.290
she switched them out and stashed them
in her secret storage vault.

00:09:20.374 --> 00:09:22.209
Inside is her collection,

00:09:22.793 --> 00:09:27.839
all gathered through embezzlement,
confiscation, and swapping.

00:09:27.923 --> 00:09:29.966
Hey!

00:09:30.050 --> 00:09:31.593
How did you obtain this video?

00:09:31.676 --> 00:09:33.637
When did you start preparing
to expose this?

00:09:33.720 --> 00:09:34.638
Chair Kim!

00:09:34.721 --> 00:09:36.139
Is there additional evidence

00:09:36.223 --> 00:09:37.974
that Chair Kim Sun-ae
committed this crime?

00:09:42.145 --> 00:09:44.481
Even Han Jin-woo,
the artist who painted this work

00:09:44.564 --> 00:09:46.525
and was regarded
as a prodigy in the art world,

00:09:46.608 --> 00:09:49.361
was reduced to a forger
because of Chair Kim.

00:09:52.114 --> 00:09:54.908
I stand here today

00:09:55.784 --> 00:09:59.788
to restore the honor of an artist
who passed away in disgrace.

00:10:00.372 --> 00:10:01.540
Even at this moment,

00:10:01.623 --> 00:10:04.334
another forgery
is likely being created somewhere

00:10:04.418 --> 00:10:06.336
under Chair Kim's orders.

00:10:07.087 --> 00:10:10.090
Therefore, I urge the police
to conduct a thorough investigation.

00:10:19.224 --> 00:10:20.100
Hey.

00:10:20.767 --> 00:10:24.229
Do you think people will believe
a manipulated video?

00:10:29.484 --> 00:10:30.318
Ms. Kim Sun-ae.

00:10:31.361 --> 00:10:33.738
You're being arrested under a warrant
for embezzlement, fraud, and violating

00:10:33.822 --> 00:10:36.408
the Act on Regulation and Punishment
of Criminal Proceeds Concealment.

00:10:37.951 --> 00:10:39.911
-The police seem to believe it.
-Chair Kim.

00:10:40.495 --> 00:10:41.580
No, don't.

00:10:41.663 --> 00:10:43.457
I didn't do anything wrong. How dare you?

00:10:43.540 --> 00:10:45.584
You're making a mistake!

00:11:02.726 --> 00:11:03.685
What's all this?

00:11:04.519 --> 00:11:06.897
Man, an art gallery
doesn't hold a candle to this place.

00:11:07.606 --> 00:11:09.191
Just how much did she get away with?

00:11:18.742 --> 00:11:20.535
We've already collected evidence
from your suite.

00:11:21.203 --> 00:11:22.287
What?

00:11:22.370 --> 00:11:24.331
Who do you think you are, going in there?

00:11:24.414 --> 00:11:26.082
Don't you dare touch a thing!

00:11:26.708 --> 00:11:27.542
Not a single thing!

00:11:27.626 --> 00:11:30.212
Don't touch a thing! It's all mine!

00:11:31.046 --> 00:11:32.214
Don't touch anything!

00:11:32.297 --> 00:11:33.757
Don't lay a finger on anything!

00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:34.674
-It's all mine!
-Come on!

00:11:34.758 --> 00:11:35.884
Don't you dare touch anything!

00:11:35.967 --> 00:11:37.719
Hey, Han Seol-ah!

00:11:37.802 --> 00:11:38.887
You!

00:11:39.513 --> 00:11:40.972
Han Seol-ah!

00:11:44.976 --> 00:11:45.852
Let go of me!

00:11:46.811 --> 00:11:48.480
Han Seol-ah!

00:12:13.547 --> 00:12:16.508
They'll lock down the site
and control access.

00:12:17.259 --> 00:12:19.177
There are so many high-value pieces

00:12:20.053 --> 00:12:21.555
that they have to seal the vault door

00:12:22.138 --> 00:12:23.723
until they can be moved
to a secure location.

00:12:24.849 --> 00:12:27.477
We need to compare the documents
you submitted against the evidence.

00:12:28.520 --> 00:12:31.898
Could you conduct an initial review
before the professional authentication?

00:12:34.985 --> 00:12:37.529
You won't find this painting
in the documents.

00:12:37.612 --> 00:12:39.698
The original artist's name
was Han Jin-woo.

00:12:40.282 --> 00:12:41.241
He was my father.

00:12:44.369 --> 00:12:45.912
This piece can be returned, right?

00:12:46.997 --> 00:12:48.415
Help Seol-ah get it back.

00:12:49.124 --> 00:12:49.958
Okay.

00:13:00.594 --> 00:13:01.803
What's this?

00:13:01.886 --> 00:13:03.388
It's still wrapped.

00:13:12.564 --> 00:13:13.607
It's the Stiller.

00:13:14.774 --> 00:13:16.651
The painting that's worth
over 15 billion won?

00:13:18.695 --> 00:13:20.530
Did she switch this out too?

00:13:21.281 --> 00:13:23.450
It's the original piece that was
on display in the exhibition hall.

00:13:25.118 --> 00:13:28.079
Does that mean a forgery of this piece
is being created too?

00:13:41.301 --> 00:13:42.927
-Woo-seok.
-I'll call you later.

00:14:06.910 --> 00:14:08.203
Are you still at the company?

00:14:08.912 --> 00:14:10.121
We need to talk.

00:14:12.666 --> 00:14:14.334
Everyone out of the workshop.

00:14:14.918 --> 00:14:16.294
Just get out. I'll handle the rest.

00:14:17.462 --> 00:14:19.464
Just do as I say, you bastards!

00:15:34.164 --> 00:15:35.206
What the hell?

00:15:35.790 --> 00:15:37.625
Why haven't you left yet?

00:15:44.466 --> 00:15:45.675
Who is it?

00:15:58.563 --> 00:15:59.689
It's been a while,

00:16:00.523 --> 00:16:01.483
Ju Hyun-su.

00:16:02.192 --> 00:16:03.276
Damn.

00:16:04.110 --> 00:16:06.362
You were the SIU investigator
after the Taemyung pieces?

00:16:06.446 --> 00:16:08.490
There's nowhere to run now, you bastard.

00:16:08.573 --> 00:16:10.742
Get ready to rot in prison.

00:16:10.825 --> 00:16:13.411
You have nothing on me
if I burn all the evidence.

00:16:14.871 --> 00:16:16.498
Do you want to die too, you bastard?!

00:16:20.585 --> 00:16:21.753
Goddamn it.

00:16:21.836 --> 00:16:23.630
That was a confession, right?

00:16:23.713 --> 00:16:25.590
-Damn you.
-That you killed Woo-hee.

00:16:25.673 --> 00:16:28.343
My life got screwed because of that bitch!

00:16:28.426 --> 00:16:30.261
I wouldn't have messed with her
if I'd known her brother was a cop.

00:16:30.345 --> 00:16:32.555
Shut the hell up, you asshole!

00:16:33.264 --> 00:16:35.391
She didn't care about riding in a truck

00:16:35.475 --> 00:16:36.976
and begged to ride along on my trips.

00:16:37.477 --> 00:16:40.146
She was starved for affection
and so needy.

00:16:41.523 --> 00:16:43.316
I said shut the hell up,
you son of a bitch!

00:16:58.790 --> 00:16:59.666
Get up.

00:17:07.715 --> 00:17:10.844
She was still young,
but said we should get married

00:17:10.927 --> 00:17:12.762
so she wouldn't be a burden on you.

00:17:12.846 --> 00:17:13.847
Did you know that?

00:17:15.014 --> 00:17:17.934
It's your fault she died.

00:17:18.017 --> 00:17:19.352
No.

00:17:19.435 --> 00:17:20.728
That's not true!

00:17:22.981 --> 00:17:24.023
You're wrong!

00:17:24.107 --> 00:17:25.775
You asshole!

00:17:25.859 --> 00:17:27.026
-Die, you son of a bitch!
-Woo-seok!

00:17:27.110 --> 00:17:28.820
-Hey, Cha Woo-seok!
-Woo-seok!

00:17:29.529 --> 00:17:30.446
Stop!

00:17:30.989 --> 00:17:33.825
-Stop!
-Woo-seok, stop.

00:17:33.908 --> 00:17:34.868
Stop.

00:17:36.452 --> 00:17:37.412
Please stop.

00:17:45.712 --> 00:17:46.546
Come on.

00:17:48.506 --> 00:17:49.382
Let's go.

00:18:18.077 --> 00:18:19.454
It's over now.

00:18:21.080 --> 00:18:21.956
You can let it go.

00:18:31.049 --> 00:18:32.008
It was me.

00:18:34.469 --> 00:18:36.304
I was the one who got Woo-hee killed.

00:18:37.722 --> 00:18:39.349
It was all me.

00:18:43.311 --> 00:18:44.854
Remember what you told me?

00:18:46.272 --> 00:18:47.565
You said it wasn't my fault.

00:18:48.691 --> 00:18:51.235
I'm going to say it back to you.

00:18:52.570 --> 00:18:54.280
It wasn't your fault, Woo-seok.

00:18:55.073 --> 00:18:55.907
You…

00:18:57.075 --> 00:18:58.868
always did your best.

00:19:43.079 --> 00:19:45.039
Please don't get hurt.

00:19:47.625 --> 00:19:50.753
You're the only family I have left.

00:20:16.654 --> 00:20:19.449
It's your fault she died.

00:20:34.547 --> 00:20:35.673
Name?

00:20:35.757 --> 00:20:36.883
Obviously, Ju Hyun-su.

00:20:36.966 --> 00:20:38.009
STATEMENT

00:20:38.092 --> 00:20:39.260
Date of birth?

00:20:43.306 --> 00:20:46.184
Hey, you think you can pull that
right-to-remain-silent crap on me?

00:20:51.939 --> 00:20:52.774
Damn it.

00:20:52.857 --> 00:20:55.485
This is Cha Woo-hee's case file
that I've kept for six years.

00:20:55.568 --> 00:20:58.279
When Cha Woo-seok was raging and pleading

00:20:59.697 --> 00:21:01.699
that you were the one
who killed his sister,

00:21:02.325 --> 00:21:03.618
I just scoffed at him.

00:21:04.202 --> 00:21:07.371
I told him he was just being emotional
because the victim was his sister.

00:21:07.455 --> 00:21:09.582
There's no way a guy
who's already killed someone

00:21:09.665 --> 00:21:11.042
has only been making forgeries
all this time.

00:21:12.293 --> 00:21:14.087
Tell me, you bastard!

00:21:14.170 --> 00:21:15.379
What else did Chair Kim make you do?

00:21:15.463 --> 00:21:16.839
You killed Paek Jun-beom, didn't you?

00:21:16.923 --> 00:21:18.633
No! That wasn't me!

00:21:20.384 --> 00:21:21.552
Then who did you kill?

00:21:22.887 --> 00:21:24.222
Did you kill Cha Woo-hee?

00:21:26.557 --> 00:21:27.767
Did you kill Kim Yun-ji?

00:21:29.102 --> 00:21:31.187
Shit.

00:21:46.160 --> 00:21:47.537
What's all this?

00:21:48.287 --> 00:21:50.081
I wanted to make you something to eat.

00:21:50.164 --> 00:21:52.041
You don't have to do that.

00:21:52.125 --> 00:21:54.168
I know it's hard for you
to be around fire.

00:21:54.961 --> 00:21:57.171
It's an induction stove,
so I think I can manage.

00:21:58.631 --> 00:21:59.799
You really don't have to.

00:22:00.716 --> 00:22:02.009
Should I wash this first?

00:22:04.512 --> 00:22:06.097
Go get some rest.

00:22:06.180 --> 00:22:07.723
You've been through a lot today.

00:22:16.107 --> 00:22:19.026
I'm not good at cooking,

00:22:20.611 --> 00:22:23.406
especially when someone is watching me.

00:22:40.715 --> 00:22:41.924
CARROT

00:22:43.926 --> 00:22:45.052
GREEN ONION

00:22:57.106 --> 00:22:58.524
ADD THE BEEF

00:23:21.297 --> 00:23:22.965
I can't guarantee it'll taste good.

00:23:25.676 --> 00:23:27.303
I've never cooked porridge before.

00:23:32.183 --> 00:23:34.936
I thought it'd go down easier
than just rice.

00:23:38.940 --> 00:23:39.857
Thank you.

00:23:42.735 --> 00:23:43.736
It looks great.

00:24:04.882 --> 00:24:05.800
It's good.

00:24:14.225 --> 00:24:15.726
I often thought about the meal

00:24:17.019 --> 00:24:18.646
you made for me.

00:24:19.605 --> 00:24:21.357
After the interrogation,

00:24:21.440 --> 00:24:24.193
when everything inside me fell apart,

00:24:25.444 --> 00:24:27.697
the meal that you made me

00:24:27.780 --> 00:24:30.116
helped me get back on my feet.

00:24:34.036 --> 00:24:35.538
And then you said
you didn't want to see me again.

00:24:36.998 --> 00:24:38.291
I was afraid.

00:24:41.085 --> 00:24:42.461
I thought you might get hurt

00:24:44.088 --> 00:24:45.548
if you stayed by my side.

00:24:48.926 --> 00:24:50.011
Are you not afraid anymore?

00:24:52.555 --> 00:24:54.390
I still am.

00:24:56.350 --> 00:24:59.186
But I want to give it a try

00:25:00.730 --> 00:25:02.481
because you told me

00:25:03.107 --> 00:25:04.650
not to run away,

00:25:05.359 --> 00:25:06.736
not to push you away,

00:25:08.446 --> 00:25:10.906
and to stay by your side and protect you.

00:25:14.368 --> 00:25:17.830
I think I know how you feel right now.

00:25:21.125 --> 00:25:22.084
But still,

00:25:23.252 --> 00:25:24.920
let's keep living.

00:25:27.798 --> 00:25:30.092
I won't say things will get better.

00:25:31.802 --> 00:25:32.636
Because…

00:25:33.763 --> 00:25:36.474
we have to live with this pain
for the rest of our lives.

00:25:40.186 --> 00:25:41.437
But let's get through it together.

00:25:55.368 --> 00:25:56.327
You should eat.

00:25:58.371 --> 00:25:59.497
It's really good.

00:26:28.901 --> 00:26:30.694
We ran forensics on Chair Kim's computer

00:26:31.237 --> 00:26:33.989
and found chat records with Kim Yun-ji
on the company messenger.

00:26:34.740 --> 00:26:36.200
I think you should take a look.

00:26:36.283 --> 00:26:37.576
ASSOCIATE AUCTIONEER KIM YUN-JI

00:26:38.285 --> 00:26:39.912
About the painting my father bought,

00:26:39.995 --> 00:26:42.706
did you personally bring it in
from New York?

00:26:43.290 --> 00:26:44.125
Why do you ask?

00:26:44.208 --> 00:26:46.293
Don't you think you crossed the line?

00:26:46.377 --> 00:26:48.879
I introduced that painting to him
in good faith.

00:26:49.547 --> 00:26:50.881
Come to my suite.

00:26:50.965 --> 00:26:52.383
Let's talk in person.

00:26:54.844 --> 00:26:56.053
Funny, isn't it?

00:26:56.137 --> 00:26:59.014
The head of the NTS investigation bureau
has a daughter who's an auctioneer,

00:26:59.098 --> 00:27:01.767
yet has a forgery hanging in his house.

00:27:02.351 --> 00:27:04.311
What kind of nonsense is this?

00:27:05.479 --> 00:27:07.690
I sent it
for external authentication twice,

00:27:07.773 --> 00:27:08.858
but the results were the same.

00:27:09.442 --> 00:27:10.776
I wonder what will happen

00:27:11.694 --> 00:27:13.612
when my father finds out.

00:27:14.196 --> 00:27:15.698
Are you threatening me?

00:27:16.949 --> 00:27:18.826
I'm suggesting
we try to solve the problem.

00:27:19.910 --> 00:27:21.078
What do you want?

00:27:22.496 --> 00:27:23.664
The main podium.

00:27:27.334 --> 00:27:28.752
In other words, get rid of Ms. Han?

00:27:30.504 --> 00:27:33.048
Chair Kim probably felt a lot of pressure.

00:27:34.258 --> 00:27:35.759
She would've been hit
with multiple tax evasion charges.

00:27:35.843 --> 00:27:38.137
This could've been the motive
for killing Kim Yun-ji.

00:27:46.061 --> 00:27:48.022
The Taemyung paintings
that went up in flames

00:27:48.814 --> 00:27:51.192
turned up in your secret storage vault,
and you claim ignorance?

00:27:52.651 --> 00:27:54.153
My client stored the paintings

00:27:54.236 --> 00:27:56.405
upon the client's request.

00:27:56.489 --> 00:28:00.451
The issue here is Taemyung's mismanagement
and insurance handling,

00:28:00.534 --> 00:28:02.411
not any criminal conduct by my client.

00:28:04.455 --> 00:28:06.081
Then let's talk about this.

00:28:06.707 --> 00:28:09.210
The Stiller is worth over 10 billion won,

00:28:09.835 --> 00:28:12.379
and you took advantage
of the owner's death to take it.

00:28:14.840 --> 00:28:15.841
It's the same thing.

00:28:17.134 --> 00:28:20.554
My client merely kept the painting
safely in the vault

00:28:20.638 --> 00:28:23.140
until the inheritance process
was completed.

00:28:24.016 --> 00:28:25.184
That's standard practice.

00:28:25.684 --> 00:28:28.145
Then why did she make a forgery?

00:28:30.064 --> 00:28:31.065
Why go through the trouble?

00:28:32.816 --> 00:28:35.694
Your lackey, Ju Hyun-su,
has been arrested.

00:28:39.323 --> 00:28:41.200
There's no point in holding out,

00:28:41.784 --> 00:28:42.618
Ms. Kim Sun-ae.

00:28:45.412 --> 00:28:47.248
I don't like your tone.

00:28:47.873 --> 00:28:49.458
It's very rude.

00:28:50.167 --> 00:28:51.126
Listen, Detective.

00:28:51.835 --> 00:28:54.171
Did you know who you were dealing with
when you brought me in?

00:28:55.756 --> 00:28:59.802
Well, you can't undo a mistake
that's already been made.

00:29:00.302 --> 00:29:02.304
Your future in the force

00:29:03.556 --> 00:29:06.433
could be an easy road or a difficult one.

00:29:06.517 --> 00:29:08.936
This is a critical moment for you.

00:29:09.770 --> 00:29:11.272
Don't you get it?

00:29:11.355 --> 00:29:12.898
Worry about yourself.

00:29:13.983 --> 00:29:15.985
Insurance fraud, embezzlement,

00:29:16.068 --> 00:29:17.611
dealing in forgeries,

00:29:17.695 --> 00:29:18.904
and the cherry on top.

00:29:19.780 --> 00:29:20.990
Murder for hire.

00:29:27.162 --> 00:29:29.290
You've got some nerve, don't you?

00:29:30.249 --> 00:29:32.042
Your lack of gratitude is impressive.

00:29:32.126 --> 00:29:33.836
How dare you stab Chair Kim in the back?

00:29:35.462 --> 00:29:36.880
What are you really up to?

00:29:37.548 --> 00:29:39.883
Is the plan to take over her position
while she's not here?

00:29:40.759 --> 00:29:42.511
That's probably what you want to do.

00:29:43.387 --> 00:29:45.598
How dare you accuse me of that?

00:29:45.681 --> 00:29:46.515
Hey.

00:29:47.266 --> 00:29:48.350
I'm not like you.

00:29:49.852 --> 00:29:51.478
I'm doing everything I can

00:29:51.562 --> 00:29:53.897
to handle the situation from my position.

00:29:54.607 --> 00:29:57.234
I have to take responsibility
for what I've done, don't I?

00:30:01.947 --> 00:30:02.865
Fine.

00:30:03.365 --> 00:30:05.492
I don't know how long you'll last,
but good luck with that.

00:30:06.410 --> 00:30:07.953
Chair Kim will be back soon enough.

00:30:12.124 --> 00:30:14.084
The remaining auctions
will fall through, right?

00:30:14.168 --> 00:30:16.503
These are all the client complaints
we received this morning.

00:30:16.587 --> 00:30:18.672
Most of these
are consignment cancellation requests.

00:30:18.756 --> 00:30:20.549
This is so annoying.

00:30:20.633 --> 00:30:21.800
Give me the list.

00:30:21.884 --> 00:30:25.012
I'll personally call the clients
to persuade them.

00:30:25.095 --> 00:30:28.098
Ms. Han, I didn't know
you'd come in today.

00:30:28.641 --> 00:30:29.475
Are you okay?

00:30:30.059 --> 00:30:32.102
I owe you all an apology.

00:30:32.186 --> 00:30:36.190
As someone who understands
how deeply you care about Royal Auction,

00:30:36.273 --> 00:30:37.775
I'm truly sorry

00:30:37.858 --> 00:30:40.152
for causing this situation.

00:30:40.986 --> 00:30:42.863
But you did the right thing.

00:30:44.740 --> 00:30:47.618
We actually think
this turned out for the better.

00:30:48.118 --> 00:30:51.080
We were unknowingly helping Chair Kim
carry out fraud,

00:30:51.163 --> 00:30:52.665
so it's a relief
that everything's come to light.

00:30:56.627 --> 00:30:58.420
The paintings are safely stored.

00:30:58.504 --> 00:31:01.256
How can I trust you after all the talk
of forgery and embezzlement?

00:31:01.340 --> 00:31:03.217
I promise to take full responsibility--

00:31:03.300 --> 00:31:04.343
I won't stand for this.

00:31:04.426 --> 00:31:06.095
I want my artwork back immediately!

00:31:06.178 --> 00:31:08.222
-I'll visit you in person.
-I don't care about compensation.

00:31:08.305 --> 00:31:10.599
I'll never do business
with you people again!

00:31:18.691 --> 00:31:20.943
KIM YEONG-EUN (VVIP)
AFTERNOON CHAMBER MUSIC (BY ELINA)

00:31:24.321 --> 00:31:26.073
Ms. Han.

00:31:27.116 --> 00:31:28.283
It's about Artist Han Jin-woo.

00:31:29.034 --> 00:31:31.161
You said he was family, right?

00:31:32.955 --> 00:31:33.789
Yeah.

00:31:34.331 --> 00:31:35.541
He was my father.

00:31:37.042 --> 00:31:39.712
I didn't know you carried
such a painful memory.

00:31:41.004 --> 00:31:43.966
I'm sorry I couldn't do more
to be of support.

00:31:44.675 --> 00:31:45.926
Thank you for saying that.

00:31:46.009 --> 00:31:48.470
I came to work prepared
for people to chew me out,

00:31:48.554 --> 00:31:50.097
but you've been so kind.

00:31:50.681 --> 00:31:51.515
I can't imagine

00:31:52.766 --> 00:31:54.059
how hard it must've been for you.

00:31:55.227 --> 00:31:57.604
Things will only get harder for everyone
from here on out.

00:31:57.688 --> 00:31:58.814
We'll do whatever it takes.

00:31:59.314 --> 00:32:01.400
We're ready for anything.

00:32:12.661 --> 00:32:14.663
I thought you were the only one
who really cared.

00:32:15.789 --> 00:32:17.249
But it turns out,
Han Seol-ah really cares too.

00:32:19.752 --> 00:32:23.839
It gives me chills just imagining
what could've happened if we'd been late.

00:32:24.506 --> 00:32:25.507
Make Ju Hyun-su pay

00:32:26.675 --> 00:32:27.801
for what he did.

00:32:29.178 --> 00:32:31.472
The captain is even more furious
about that than I am.

00:32:31.555 --> 00:32:33.599
I think he feels really guilty.

00:32:35.809 --> 00:32:38.353
Have that bastard and Chair Kim
confessed yet?

00:32:38.937 --> 00:32:39.897
We'll make them confess.

00:32:40.439 --> 00:32:41.815
But do you really think

00:32:41.899 --> 00:32:44.485
Chair Kim would kill someone
over a painting?

00:32:44.568 --> 00:32:47.029
She's the only suspect
who has a clear motive to kill.

00:32:47.112 --> 00:32:48.280
She might not have done it herself,

00:32:48.363 --> 00:32:50.115
but she could've hired Ju Hyun-su
to do it.

00:32:51.033 --> 00:32:52.868
He was out of the country for a long time,

00:32:52.951 --> 00:32:55.788
and there's no reason for Chair Kim
to go after Han Seol-ah's men.

00:32:57.831 --> 00:33:00.292
I have my suspicions about Do Eun-hyuk,

00:33:00.375 --> 00:33:01.585
but his alibi is solid.

00:33:05.088 --> 00:33:07.758
CCTV footage shows that Do Eun-hyuk
was at his studio in Cheongun

00:33:07.841 --> 00:33:10.427
at the time of Paek Jun-beom's murder.

00:33:11.386 --> 00:33:12.721
I want to see it.

00:33:12.805 --> 00:33:14.556
Don't ask for official records.

00:33:14.640 --> 00:33:17.351
And I want the records
of Paek Jun-beom stalking Han Seol-ah

00:33:17.434 --> 00:33:19.269
that were seized from his house,

00:33:19.353 --> 00:33:20.938
along with the photos taken in Cheongun.

00:33:24.733 --> 00:33:25.651
Please.

00:33:43.669 --> 00:33:45.838
Cell tower records show that Do Eun-hyuk
was at his studio in Cheongun

00:33:46.380 --> 00:33:48.841
at the time of Paek Jun-beom's murder.

00:33:52.553 --> 00:33:54.847
Now I understand

00:33:56.098 --> 00:33:57.224
why you trusted Cha Woo-seok.

00:33:58.976 --> 00:34:01.436
I never imagined someone like Chair Kim

00:34:02.354 --> 00:34:03.897
could get arrested.

00:34:04.773 --> 00:34:05.691
That's when it hit me

00:34:06.608 --> 00:34:08.443
that you joined hands with Cha Woo-seok

00:34:09.528 --> 00:34:12.155
because it wasn't something
I could help you with.

00:34:13.073 --> 00:34:14.157
That wasn't why.

00:34:15.117 --> 00:34:18.078
There was something we had to do,

00:34:18.704 --> 00:34:20.873
and when things overlapped along the way,

00:34:22.457 --> 00:34:24.001
we combined our efforts.

00:34:26.837 --> 00:34:28.672
That makes your relationship
even more special.

00:34:29.423 --> 00:34:30.757
Maybe it was fate.

00:34:32.551 --> 00:34:33.760
What do you think of him?

00:34:35.971 --> 00:34:37.389
You've got a good eye for people.

00:34:47.441 --> 00:34:49.401
He's the kind of person
who belongs in the center of the frame.

00:34:51.528 --> 00:34:52.946
He's confident and straightforward.

00:34:54.323 --> 00:34:55.449
But I'm the opposite.

00:34:57.409 --> 00:34:59.661
I'm someone who fits better
outside the frame.

00:35:02.831 --> 00:35:06.418
I've acted like it wasn't true
all this time,

00:35:08.629 --> 00:35:10.088
but now I'm sure of it.

00:35:12.341 --> 00:35:13.800
Why would you think that?

00:35:16.345 --> 00:35:17.346
People end up living…

00:35:19.389 --> 00:35:21.808
the way their hands have been trained.

00:35:25.646 --> 00:35:27.606
Anyway, you've been through a lot
to get this far.

00:35:28.565 --> 00:35:29.650
I'm sure it'll all work out.

00:35:30.233 --> 00:35:32.861
And I hope you can get back
Mr. Han's painting.

00:35:33.904 --> 00:35:35.030
I still feel uneasy.

00:35:35.989 --> 00:35:39.368
Chair Kim isn't the type of person
to take things lying down.

00:35:41.620 --> 00:35:42.621
Don't worry.

00:35:44.498 --> 00:35:46.291
It'll all work out the way you want.

00:36:28.125 --> 00:36:29.209
Ms. Han.

00:36:29.292 --> 00:36:30.502
Chair Kim is here.

00:36:34.047 --> 00:36:35.132
SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

00:36:35.215 --> 00:36:38.635
She's not a flight risk
and has health issues?

00:36:39.761 --> 00:36:41.013
It's always the same thing.

00:36:41.096 --> 00:36:42.848
You've got to be kidding me.

00:36:43.432 --> 00:36:45.058
She brought in another top law firm,

00:36:45.142 --> 00:36:46.852
and sure enough,
they kept her out of custody.

00:37:10.542 --> 00:37:11.501
Take a seat.

00:37:20.135 --> 00:37:23.305
What were you thinking all this time
while working here?

00:37:24.056 --> 00:37:25.724
Have you been living
with such bitter determination

00:37:25.807 --> 00:37:29.644
just to take me down
and get revenge for your father?

00:37:31.063 --> 00:37:32.981
I learned it all from you.

00:37:39.196 --> 00:37:42.115
My father painted theater signs.

00:37:43.075 --> 00:37:45.619
I just helped him paint at first,

00:37:45.702 --> 00:37:49.706
but then I wanted to become a real artist,
so I became an apprentice.

00:37:50.791 --> 00:37:54.252
That's when I saw your father and realized

00:37:56.296 --> 00:38:00.383
that even a prodigy like him
can starve to death in this industry.

00:38:01.968 --> 00:38:04.096
Is that why you had him paint forgeries?

00:38:06.765 --> 00:38:08.975
I gave him a chance to earn a living

00:38:09.059 --> 00:38:11.061
so your family wouldn't go hungry.

00:38:11.144 --> 00:38:12.020
Hey.

00:38:12.521 --> 00:38:14.773
How is it my fault that naive man

00:38:14.856 --> 00:38:17.234
went into debt to repay everything?

00:38:17.818 --> 00:38:21.196
Do you think that justifies
causing someone's death?

00:38:21.279 --> 00:38:24.241
I didn't cause it! It was his choice!

00:38:24.324 --> 00:38:28.829
I was the one who called 119
when your house caught on fire.

00:38:28.912 --> 00:38:30.705
I was the one who saved your life!

00:38:30.789 --> 00:38:32.707
You should've left me to die!

00:38:35.210 --> 00:38:37.254
Then I wouldn't be in so much pain.

00:38:38.463 --> 00:38:40.882
I had to grovel before you like a dog

00:38:41.466 --> 00:38:43.969
and constantly force a smile

00:38:44.052 --> 00:38:45.887
for living at the price
of my parents' lives.

00:38:48.932 --> 00:38:50.392
Even if you manage to get out of this,

00:38:51.893 --> 00:38:54.479
I'll hunt you down to the very end.

00:38:59.317 --> 00:39:00.861
What else can you possibly do?

00:39:02.028 --> 00:39:04.906
All the judges and prosecutors
are in my pocket.

00:39:06.074 --> 00:39:09.161
A dog might get away
with biting its owner once,

00:39:09.661 --> 00:39:10.495
but do it again,

00:39:11.454 --> 00:39:13.373
and it'll be beaten to death.

00:39:15.959 --> 00:39:18.420
I'll have to go for the neck, then.

00:39:22.132 --> 00:39:24.426
You think you'll get a chance to do that?

00:39:25.093 --> 00:39:28.346
It'll be your neck on the line.

00:39:33.518 --> 00:39:34.811
I guess

00:39:35.645 --> 00:39:37.689
we'll just have to wait and see…

00:39:40.275 --> 00:39:41.735
whose neck is on the line.

00:40:24.527 --> 00:40:25.987
Ju Hyun-su will be out soon.

00:40:26.529 --> 00:40:28.782
Take care of that bastard quietly first.

00:40:28.865 --> 00:40:29.866
If you don't,

00:40:31.534 --> 00:40:34.746
I'll make sure she finds out
about the secret

00:40:34.829 --> 00:40:36.581
you're so desperate to keep from her.

00:41:08.571 --> 00:41:10.448
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

00:41:35.098 --> 00:41:40.478
And even if it costs me my life, Llorona

00:41:43.273 --> 00:41:48.069
I will not stop loving you

00:42:10.884 --> 00:42:12.135
…Llorona…

00:42:17.932 --> 00:42:23.480
Ah, woe is me, Llorona, Llorona

00:42:28.818 --> 00:42:33.823
Ah, woe is me, Llorona, Llorona

00:43:02.644 --> 00:43:08.525
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:43:51.734 --> 00:43:53.611
Everything is too perfect.

00:44:16.843 --> 00:44:17.677
Where are you going?

00:44:20.597 --> 00:44:21.639
To see Chair Kim.

00:44:22.223 --> 00:44:23.266
Did she ask to see you?

00:44:24.017 --> 00:44:24.851
No.

00:44:26.519 --> 00:44:28.146
I'm telling her that I'm quitting.

00:44:29.856 --> 00:44:31.524
I wanted to take responsibility

00:44:32.692 --> 00:44:35.153
and make things right
regarding the last auction,

00:44:35.653 --> 00:44:37.489
-but Chair Kim--
-She'd never let that slide.

00:44:38.740 --> 00:44:39.616
Let's go together.

00:44:39.699 --> 00:44:41.242
I'm quitting too.

00:44:42.035 --> 00:44:44.162
I told you not to do that.

00:44:44.245 --> 00:44:45.205
Don't get it wrong.

00:44:45.955 --> 00:44:47.790
I want to focus on my own work now

00:44:47.874 --> 00:44:49.501
and get back in the water.

00:47:02.884 --> 00:47:04.010
The security guard said

00:47:04.093 --> 00:47:06.012
he heard music playing
into the early hours.

00:47:06.638 --> 00:47:08.765
The first to discover her
were Han Seol-ah and Do Eun-hyuk.

00:47:08.848 --> 00:47:10.975
-Any signs of foul play?
-Not yet.

00:47:11.559 --> 00:47:13.895
There's a suicide note on her laptop,

00:47:13.978 --> 00:47:16.022
but it's not enough
to rule this a suicide.

00:47:16.522 --> 00:47:19.233
The CCTVs near the suite don't work.

00:47:20.735 --> 00:47:22.987
Well, she had to move the paintings
into the storage vault secretly.

00:47:24.530 --> 00:47:25.907
And now her death

00:47:26.574 --> 00:47:27.617
has become a secret too.

00:47:33.414 --> 00:47:35.833
HAN SEOL-AH

00:47:35.917 --> 00:47:38.586
Your call cannot be connected.

00:48:58.875 --> 00:49:01.794
This isn't the outcome I was hoping for.

00:49:03.004 --> 00:49:05.631
Chair Kim would never commit suicide.

00:49:05.715 --> 00:49:07.633
When I saw her the day before,

00:49:07.717 --> 00:49:09.469
she showed no signs of guilt

00:49:09.552 --> 00:49:11.012
and was self-assured.

00:49:12.597 --> 00:49:15.558
I think someone went through
the chair's suite.

00:49:17.894 --> 00:49:20.521
And it's strange that she left
the suicide note on her laptop,

00:49:21.105 --> 00:49:24.484
considering that she still keeps
handwritten ledgers.

00:49:28.738 --> 00:49:30.281
Does that mean Chair Kim was also…

00:49:31.866 --> 00:49:33.284
It's all connected.

00:49:34.952 --> 00:49:36.078
I feel like

00:49:37.205 --> 00:49:39.081
this is all the work of one person.

00:49:39.957 --> 00:49:41.709
This isn't over

00:49:42.293 --> 00:49:43.836
until we catch the killer.

00:49:54.931 --> 00:49:55.973
Are you okay?

00:49:58.059 --> 00:49:59.268
You'll hurt yourself. I'll do it.

00:50:26.337 --> 00:50:27.255
Dear Seol-ah,

00:50:28.548 --> 00:50:31.759
I hope the day you read this never comes.

00:50:33.845 --> 00:50:35.221
A woman came to see me

00:50:36.264 --> 00:50:38.057
and told me some strange things about you.

00:50:39.809 --> 00:50:41.310
To be honest, I was swayed by her words.

00:50:54.866 --> 00:50:56.534
This is Seung-jae's handwriting.

00:50:59.412 --> 00:51:01.080
He left a clue about the culprit.

00:51:14.927 --> 00:51:15.970
Are you okay?

00:51:19.181 --> 00:51:20.057
Seol-ah.

00:51:46.709 --> 00:51:47.668
INSURANCE APPLICATION FORM

00:51:48.920 --> 00:51:51.005
INSURANCE AGENT: KIM MI-SUK

00:51:57.678 --> 00:51:59.805
This is your parents'
life insurance application form.

00:52:01.933 --> 00:52:03.434
Look at the agent's name.

00:52:05.436 --> 00:52:06.854
I think it might be someone you know.

00:52:06.938 --> 00:52:08.272
INSURANCE AGENT: KIM MI-SUK

00:52:22.578 --> 00:52:24.497
These are photos
from Paek Jun-beom's house.

00:52:25.831 --> 00:52:27.166
I hadn't looked closely before,

00:52:27.667 --> 00:52:29.126
but Kim Yun-ji was in some of them.

00:52:33.464 --> 00:52:35.049
So she was in Cheongun

00:52:35.841 --> 00:52:37.593
the day before Seung-jae died.

00:52:38.594 --> 00:52:39.971
She stayed until the next morning.

00:52:43.391 --> 00:52:46.102
This photo
was taken by the river that day.

00:52:55.403 --> 00:52:58.406
Kim Yun-ji was a witness.

00:53:00.408 --> 00:53:02.535
She knew who killed Seung-jae.

00:53:03.619 --> 00:53:05.246
And that's why she was killed.

00:53:09.667 --> 00:53:11.502
Can this be used as evidence?

00:53:12.003 --> 00:53:13.462
It's not enough,

00:53:14.422 --> 00:53:15.881
but they'll show up in front of me soon

00:53:16.924 --> 00:53:18.259
because I'm Han Seol-ah's man

00:53:19.093 --> 00:53:20.386
who knows their secret.

00:53:21.470 --> 00:53:22.722
If we use this opportunity to--

00:53:22.805 --> 00:53:23.639
No.

00:53:23.723 --> 00:53:25.808
I won't use you as bait.

00:53:25.891 --> 00:53:29.603
I'm the only one who can approach them
without raising suspicion.

00:53:29.687 --> 00:53:31.605
-I'll do it.
-It's too dangerous.

00:53:31.689 --> 00:53:32.857
Even Chair Kim is dead.

00:53:32.940 --> 00:53:34.108
What's dangerous

00:53:34.191 --> 00:53:37.153
is always feeling on edge
and shaking in fear.

00:53:37.236 --> 00:53:38.988
I won't live like that anymore.

00:53:39.071 --> 00:53:40.489
Then let's go together.

00:53:40.573 --> 00:53:42.033
We'll get caught if we do.

00:53:45.786 --> 00:53:48.289
You need to confirm something too, right?

00:53:49.540 --> 00:53:50.541
Then at least tell me your route.

00:53:51.459 --> 00:53:53.377
I'll also keep you updated
whenever I'm on the move.

00:53:56.881 --> 00:53:57.798
Be careful.

